===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|emeraude}}, borrowed from {{der|en|fro|esmeraude}}, from {{der|en|VL.|*smaralda}}, {{m|la|*smaraldus}}, {{m|la|*smaraudus}}, variant of {{der|en|la|smaragdus}}, from {{der|en|grc|σμάραγδος}}, {{m|grc|μάραγδος}}, from a {{der|en|sem|-}} language. Compare {{cog|he|בָּרֶקֶת|tr=bareket||emerald, flashing gem}}, {{cog|akk|𒁀𒊏𒄣|tr=baraqu|lit=scintillation}}, {{cog|ar|بَرْق|lit=flashing}}, {{cog|egy|bwyrqꜣ|lit=to sparkle}}:<hiero>D58-Z7-Z4:D21-N29-Z1-G1-D6</hiero> and loanwords with Semitic etymon such as {{cog|sa|मरकत}} and {{cog|fa|زمرد|tr=zomorrod}} (whence {{cog|tr|zümrüt}} and {{cog|ru|изумру́д}}).

